00:16:12,470 --> 00:16:14,510
One sec...

264
00:16:14,510 --> 00:16:16,100
Excuse me.

265
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:17,770
<i>[Junko]</i>

266
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:21,610
Hello?

267
00:16:24,540 --> 00:16:27,030
What?! He proposed?

268
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:30,480
That seven-seconds man?

269
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:31,930
Excuse me.

270
00:16:31,930 --> 00:16:34,690
You have to tell me everything later.

271
00:16:34,690 --> 00:16:37,010
Okay, bye.

272
00:16:37,590 --> 00:16:39,530
Sorry about that.

273
00:16:39,530 --> 00:16:41,280
My childhood friend

274
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:43,490
was just proposed to by her cousin.

275
00:16:43,490 --> 00:16:46,310
I was so shocked.

276
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:48,310
Proposed?

277
00:16:48,310 --> 00:16:50,070
Yes!

278
00:16:50,070 --> 00:16:51,800
And the guy who proposed

279
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:55,460
was my classmate in middle school, so I was so surprised.

280
00:16:55,460 --> 00:16:58,950
He is an elite who went to the University of Tokyo and works at a trading company now.

281
00:16:58,950 --> 00:17:01,060
- A trading company?
- Yes.

282
00:17:01,060 --> 00:17:02,740
But he's clueless when it comes to love.

283
00:17:02,740 --> 00:17:05,470
He's had a crush on her for twenty years

284
00:17:05,470 --> 00:17:08,970
and he finally proposed.

285
00:17:08,970 --> 00:17:11,080
- To his cousin?
- Yes.

286
00:17:13,590 --> 00:17:15,790
- Huh?
- Oh my.

287
00:17:15,790 --> 00:17:18,740
I just thought he sounds very familiar.

288
00:17:18,740 --> 00:17:20,890
- At my company-
- Huh?

289
00:17:22,830 --> 00:17:26,190
A senior at my dance company.

290
00:17:26,190 --> 00:17:29,810
- He's had a crush on his cousin for a while, too.
- What?

291
00:17:29,810 --> 00:17:32,480
He's shockingly hopeless with love.

292
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:35,780
When he confessed his feelings, she didn't even notice it.

293
00:17:40,950 --> 00:17:45,180
They're so similar! I guess it's kind of common!

294
00:17:45,180 --> 00:17:48,400
- Shall we eat?
- Yes, let's eat.

295
00:17:49,660 --> 00:17:53,080
Oh my!  I wrapped up the date early for you!

296
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:56,020
Tell me everything!

297
00:17:56,020 --> 00:17:57,940
It happened here?

298
00:17:57,940 --> 00:18:00,570
He kissed you here?

299
00:18:01,610 --> 00:18:03,510
H-Hold on...

300
00:18:06,060 --> 00:18:08,850
So tell me. How was it?

301
00:18:08,850 --> 00:18:12,210
How was it? That's not important.

302
00:18:12,210 --> 00:18:15,000
Of course, it is. When he kissed you-

303
00:18:15,860 --> 00:18:18,510
Did you hate it? Did it make your heart flutter?

304
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:22,710
If you were a woman, you should know the answer based on your feelings.

305
00:18:23,820 --> 00:18:25,840
I was too surprised.

306
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:27,700
I aged overnight!

307
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:31,750
- What are you talking about? Come on, now!
- Stop!

308
00:18:31,750 --> 00:18:34,100
You're enjoying this too much.

309
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:37,320
Come on! He was so close to becoming

310
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:39,100
a spineless, good-for-nothing hermit,

311
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:42,580
and then he kisses you and proposes!

312
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:46,280
Is he on his death bed?

313
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:48,910
I'm getting worried now.

314
00:18:48,910 --> 00:18:52,260
He's transferring to Russia in April.

315
00:18:53,060 --> 00:18:55,140
So that's why.

316
00:18:56,890 --> 00:18:58,520
So?

317
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:02,580
I can't give him an answer that fast.

318
00:19:02,580 --> 00:19:05,900
Masashi wants me to think it over well.

319
00:19:09,580 --> 00:19:14,290
What do I do? How am I supposed to act around him now?

320
00:19:14,290 --> 00:19:15,790
If my parents found out,

321
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:19,260
things would get awkward around relatives.

322
00:19:20,490 --> 00:19:22,650
What a bummer.

323
00:19:22,650 --> 00:19:24,000
What?

324
00:19:24,770 --> 00:19:27,330
Stop acting like you're considering his feelings.

325
00:19:27,330 --> 00:19:30,380
Just be honest with yourself.

326
00:19:30,380 --> 00:19:32,850
Both Yakumo and Yamashita

327
00:19:32,850 --> 00:19:35,850
put themselves out there for you.

328
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:38,970
Haven't you ever wanted

329
00:19:38,970 --> 00:19:41,550
to answer their feelings?

330
00:19:45,900 --> 00:19:48,130
Think about it carefully

331
00:19:48,130 --> 00:19:50,540
and choose wisely.

332
00:19:50,540 --> 00:19:53,070
Whichever you choose.

333
00:19:53,610 --> 00:19:56,120
- Whichever?
- Right.

