00:20:13,460 --> 00:20:15,610
<i>It's so cold here!</i>

338
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:19,610
Work, work...

339
00:20:19,610 --> 00:20:23,740
Gori, thanks for letting me use your place.

340
00:20:24,780 --> 00:20:26,900
Okay...

341
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:32,480
I thought we'd add a last-minute review starting this week.

342
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:35,040
- What about English?
- We'll work on his time management

343
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:37,030
through the practice exam.

344
00:20:37,030 --> 00:20:38,980
And his Japanese?

345
00:20:38,980 --> 00:20:41,470
We'll focus on Chinese literature and classical literature during the New Year's holiday.

346
00:20:41,470 --> 00:20:44,660
- What's going on with Yakumo?
- For world history...

347
00:20:47,210 --> 00:20:49,520
You haven't done it yet?

348
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:51,610
What are you talking about?

349
00:20:51,610 --> 00:20:53,770
He even went to your place.

350
00:20:53,770 --> 00:20:55,720
Something must be going on.

351
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:57,210
Not really...

352
00:20:57,210 --> 00:21:00,070
I just want to know.

353
00:21:00,070 --> 00:21:02,080
If Yakumo is a free man,

354
00:21:02,080 --> 00:21:05,670
there are lots of different ways I could come onto him.

355
00:21:05,670 --> 00:21:09,520
We don't have time to waste now that we're over 30.

356
00:21:10,510 --> 00:21:14,080
So? Can I go for Yakumo?

357
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:20,690
He asked me to marry him the other day.

358
00:21:20,690 --> 00:21:24,020
What on earth?

359
00:21:24,970 --> 00:21:28,830
Only if we had been reunited a little sooner...

360
00:21:28,830 --> 00:21:34,210
He hasn't made a move in twenty years. Why now?

361
00:21:34,790 --> 00:21:38,030
I'm so jealous. What a turnaround.

362
00:21:38,030 --> 00:21:40,420
Marrying someone who's known you for ages,

363
00:21:40,420 --> 00:21:43,200
and he's earnest and successful.

364
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:45,590
It's perfect.

365
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:49,150
- I haven't decided to marry him.
- Huh?

366
00:21:49,150 --> 00:21:51,160
What's there to think about?

367
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:54,040
Do you think a nerd like you who has never dated

368
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:57,840
will find a better guy along the line?

369
00:21:57,840 --> 00:21:59,960
Wait! Don't say it like that!

370
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:01,440
Don't tell me...

371
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:04,210
you're interested in Yuri.

372
00:22:05,490 --> 00:22:07,590
He's interested in you, right?

373
00:22:07,590 --> 00:22:09,570
That kid.

374
00:22:09,570 --> 00:22:12,490
Are you interested in him too?

375
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:16,570
That's crazy. He's my student.

376
00:22:16,570 --> 00:22:18,420
Then take a carrot,

377
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:21,860
and dangle it over his head.

378
00:22:21,860 --> 00:22:25,220
That will motivate him.

379
00:22:25,220 --> 00:22:27,460
You should let him dream.

380
00:22:27,460 --> 00:22:30,950
As long as you're not into him, it's fine.

381
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:33,620
- But...
- Just do it.

382
00:22:33,620 --> 00:22:35,900
Give him a carrot, then his grades will go up.

383
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:37,830
Plain and simple.

384
00:22:37,830 --> 00:22:41,330
He'll wake up from his dream in April.

385
00:22:44,940 --> 00:22:47,070
<i>[Hungry Jungle]</i>

386
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:53,490
Excuse me...

387
00:22:53,490 --> 00:22:55,580
What's wrong?

388
00:22:56,550 --> 00:22:59,620
A bit of a broken heart.

389
00:23:01,230 --> 00:23:05,200
I'm going to cool off my head.

390
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:07,820
Get on my shoulders, Buddy.

391
00:23:11,230 --> 00:23:15,750
The exam will have multiple-choice answer sheets like this.

392
00:23:15,750 --> 00:23:18,580
If worse comes worse, you can mark the answers without reading questions.

393
00:23:18,580 --> 00:23:20,390
So don't give up till the end.

394
00:23:20,390 --> 00:23:22,630
Answering without reading the question?

395
00:23:22,630 --> 00:23:26,480
Making a choice means eliminating the alternatives.

396
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:30,670
Just by looking at the answers, you can eliminate the wrong ones.

397
00:23:30,670 --> 00:23:32,630
Eliminate them?

398
00:23:32,630 --> 00:23:36,520
It's kind of like an urban legend, but for humanity subjects,

399
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:41,180
you can get rid of answers that don't make sense.

400
00:23:41,180 --> 00:23:46,020
You can get rid of answers that use words like "always".

401
00:23:46,020 --> 00:23:47,970
And then...

402
00:23:47,970 --> 00:23:50,570
Get rid of the first answer.

403
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:53,110
- The first answer?
- The answer is usually

404
00:23:53,110 --> 00:23:56,120
- the second or third answer.
- What?

405
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:59,030
That's what

406
00:23:59,030 --> 00:24:03,010
- people have always said.
- No way!

407
00:24:03,010 --> 00:24:06,570
Or not. That's just a rumor.

408
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:08,150
<i>[28 days until National Center Test for University Admissions]</i>

409
00:24:08,150 --> 00:24:10,620
Let's call it a day here.

410
00:24:10,620 --> 00:24:12,850
You had math tutoring too, so you must be tired.

411
00:24:12,850 --> 00:24:14,670
I'm fine.

412
00:24:15,430 --> 00:24:19,310
From now on, your health is as important as your studies.

413
00:24:19,310 --> 00:24:21,890
You must always wash your hands and gargle.

414
00:24:22,870 --> 00:24:24,940
I remember your mom was saying that, too.

415
00:24:24,940 --> 00:24:26,520
Before my exam,

416
00:24:26,520 --> 00:24:30,330
I was at my limit physically and mentally,

417
00:24:30,330 --> 00:24:32,720
and my performance suffered.

418
00:24:32,720 --> 00:24:34,620
I understand.

419
00:24:34,620 --> 00:24:36,480
For Christmas and New Year's,

420
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:39,460
I'll stay inside and study.

421
00:24:39,460 --> 00:24:40,710
<i>[Recruiting New Students]</i>

422
00:24:40,710 --> 00:24:43,200
But for the new year shrine visit,

423
00:24:43,910 --> 00:24:45,990
would you come with me?

424
00:24:46,970 --> 00:24:48,480
Please?

425
00:24:49,080 --> 00:24:50,940
<i>You should let him dream.</i>

426
00:24:50,940 --> 00:24:54,280
<i>As long as you're not really into him, it's fine.</i>

427
00:24:54,280 --> 00:24:56,480
Carrot...

428
00:25:01,770 --> 00:25:04,940
Sure. For exam takers,

429
00:25:04,940 --> 00:25:08,310
prayers and superstitions are important, right?

430
00:25:09,170 --> 00:25:10,970
Indeed.

431
00:25:12,410 --> 00:25:14,520
